" Here's the JSON object for a Python problem:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"title\": \"Unique Occurrences Checker (Hard)\",\n  \"description\": \"Given an array of integers, write a function `unique_occurrences` that checks if each number appears only once in the list. If all numbers appear exactly once, return True; otherwise, return False.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef unique_occurrences(arr: List[int]) -> bool:\\n```\\n\\n#### Inputs\\n- `arr` (List[int]): A list of integers.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns `True` if all numbers appear exactly once in the list, `False` otherwise.\\n\",\n  \"code\": \"\"\"from collections import Counter\\n\\ndef unique_occurrences(arr: List[int]) -> bool:\\n    # Count occurrences of each number using a dictionary (Counter)\\n    counts = Counter(arr)\\n    # Check if all numbers appear exactly once\\n    return all(count == 1 for count in counts.values())\\n\",\n  \"tests\": [\n    \"assert unique_([4, 5, 6]) == True\",\n    \"assert unique_([3, 2, 1, 0]) == True\",\n    \"assert unique_([7, 8, 9, 7]) == False\",\n    \"assert unique_([1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 9, 0]) == True\"\n  ]\n}\n```"